http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/IIM-B-set-for-a-star-studded-fest/article14023128.ece

Playback singer Sunidhi Chauhan, London-based metal band Metastasis, and ‘Dance India Dance’ finalist Priya Kumar Varunesh will all be marking their attendance at the Indian Institute of Management, Bangalore (IIM-B) for its annual three-day cultural festival, UNMAAD, starting Friday.With a prize money of Rs. 10 lakh at stake, IIM-B has planned a rock show, a dance, a fashion show, quizzes and even a culinary festival. This year’s theme, ‘A Breath of Life’, will also have students organising an anti-pollution drive across Bengaluru.